        class="code-comment">&#8595;</span><br>
    <span class="code-html">&lt;div/&gt;</span><br><br>
    <span class="code-language">CSS</span><br>
    <span class="code-comment">The <code>display:flex</code> property automatically sets the main axis to horizontal
        (row) by default, so there is no need to explicitly set <code>flex-direction:row;</code></span>
    <hr class="code-line">
    <span class="code-property">.container</span> {<br>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code-current-example">display</span>: <span class="code-current-example">flex</span>;<br>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code-current-example">flex-direction</span>: <span class="code-current-example">row</span>;/
    <span class="code-current-example">flex-direction</span>: <span class="code-current-example">row-reverse</span>;
    <br>
    }
</div>

